memberdef.definition: desmoj.core.simulator.EventOf2Entities< E extends Entity, F extends Entity >.EventOf2Entities
memberdef.name: EventOf2Entities

detaileddescription.para: Creates a new Event of the given model, with the given name and trace option.

parameterdescription.para: java.lang.String : The name of this event
Model : The model this event is associated to
boolean : Flag for showing Event in trace-files. Set it to true if Event should show up in trace. Set it to false if Event should not be shown in trace.

memberdef.definition: abstract void desmoj.core.simulator.EventOf2Entities< E extends Entity, F extends Entity >.eventRoutine
memberdef.name: eventRoutine

detaileddescription.para: Implement this abstract method to express the changes of state this event does to two entities (as SimProcess is a subclass of Entity, processes can be passed as well).

For type safety, it is recommended to derive your events from the generic type EventOf2Entities<EntityType1,EntityType2> where EntityType1 and EntityType2 (which are derived from class Entity) represent the entity types your event is supposed to operate on.

Should you decide to derive your event from the raw type EventOf2Entities (which is not recommended), please take extra care in checking the given Entity parameters to your special eventRoutine since any subtype of Entity will be accepted! If your model uses several different entity types, chances are that while developing the model, wrong entity types might be passed.

parameterdescription.para: E : The first entity associated to this event.
F : The second entity associated to this event.

memberdef.definition: void desmoj.core.simulator.EventOf2Entities< E extends Entity, F extends Entity >.schedule
memberdef.name: schedule

detaileddescription.para: Schedules this event to act on the given entities at a certain point in simulation time.

parameterdescription.para: E : The first entity to be manipulated by this event
F : The second entity to be manipulated by this event
TimeInstant : The point in simulation time this event is scheduled to happen.

memberdef.definition: void desmoj.core.simulator.EventOf2Entities< E extends Entity, F extends Entity >.schedule
memberdef.name: schedule

detaileddescription.para: Schedules this event to act the given entities at the specified point in simulation time. The point of time is given as an offset to the current simulation time as displayed by the simulation clock.

parameterdescription.para: E : The first entity this event happens to
F : The second entity this event happens to
TimeSpan : The offset to the current simulation time this Event is to happen

memberdef.definition: void desmoj.core.simulator.EventOf2Entities< E extends Entity, F extends Entity >.schedule
memberdef.name: schedule

detaileddescription.para: Schedules this event to act the given entities at the specified point in simulation time determined by a sample from the distribution provided to the method. The sample is interpreted as offset from the the present time in the reference time unit.

parameterdescription.para: E : The first entity this event happens to
F : The second entity this event happens to
NumericalDist<?> : Numerical distribution to sample the offset to the current simulation time from

memberdef.definition: void desmoj.core.simulator.EventOf2Entities< E extends Entity, F extends Entity >.scheduleAfter
memberdef.name: scheduleAfter

detaileddescription.para: Schedules this event to act on the given Entity directly after the given Schedulable is already set to be activated. Note that this event's point of simulation time will be set to be the same as the Schedulable's time. Thus this event will occur directly after the given Schedulable but the simulation clock will not change. Make sure that the Schedulable given as parameter is actually scheduled.

parameterdescription.para: Schedulable : The Schedulable this entity should be scheduled after
E : The first entity to be manipulated by this event
F : The second entity to be manipulated by this event

memberdef.definition: void desmoj.core.simulator.EventOf2Entities< E extends Entity, F extends Entity >.scheduleBefore
memberdef.name: scheduleBefore

detaileddescription.para: Schedules this event to act on the given Entity directly before the given Schedulable is already set to be activated. Note that this event's point of simulation time will be set to be the same as the Schedulable's time. Thus this event will occur directly before the given Schedulable but the simulation clock will not change. Make sure that the Schedulable given as parameter is actually scheduled.

parameterdescription.para: Schedulable : The Schedulable this entity should be scheduled before
E : The first entity to be manipulated by this event
F : The second entity to be manipulated by this event

memberdef.definition: EventOf2Entities<E,F> desmoj.core.simulator.EventOf2Entities< E extends Entity, F extends Entity >.clone
memberdef.name: clone

detaileddescription.para: Creates and returns a copy of this event. Note that subclasses have to implement the interface java.lang.Cloneable to actually use this method as otherwise, a CloneNotSupportedException will be thrown.

simplesect.para: EventOf2Entities<E,F> : A copy of this event.

detaileddescription.para: Provides the class for user defined events to change two entities' internal states. The state of a discrete model is changed by events that occur at distinct points of simulation time.
For events changing the state of one or three entities, refer to Event and EventOf3Entities. Events not associated to a specific entity are based on ExternalEvent.
For type safety it is recommended to generically assign the entity types an EventOf2Entities operates on by using the generic type EventOf2Entities<E,F> where E and F are derived from Entity.
All event object should be used only once. Implement the changes of state for the specific entities associated with this event by overriding the abstract method eventRoutine(E who1, F who2).
